  "body": "### Description of the Issue\r\n\r\nThis one's kind of tricky and I haven't been able to pin down precise steps, but sometimes when switching from ETH -> token or token -> ETH, the transaction gets reset (nonce included) but the nonce isn't re-fetched. I think this requires generating the transaction, but I'm not 100% sure. Either way, this doesn't happen easily, so I don't think it's a show-stopper.\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Unlock a wallet with a token balance\r\n2. Fill out transaction (to address, amount)\r\n3. Generate the transaction\r\n4. Switch to token\r\n5. Fill out transaction again (to address, amount)\r\n6. Send button is disabled due to lack of nonce\r\n\r\n## Console Logs / Screenshots\r\n\r\n### Actions Triggered\r\n\r\n<img width=\"375\" alt=\"screen shot 2018-04-30 at 5 08 00 pm\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/649992/39455798-7621036a-4cb0-11e8-94c7-b8becee590fc.png\">\r\n\r\n\r\n### Disabled State\r\n\r\n<img width=\"779\" alt=\"screen shot 2018-04-30 at 5 00 39 pm\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/649992/39455791-6bfc286a-4cb0-11e8-8588-269bc9c1272f.png\">\r\n",
